  "ground_truth": {
    "title": "Top 10 Live Streaming Platforms (+ How to Choose the Right One)",
    "author": "Kendall Breitman",
    "publish_date": "2025-12-03",
    "main_content": "With so many live streaming platforms built for different purposes, choosing where to go live can feel confusing. But it doesn't have to be overwhelming. In this guide, I'll give you a clear overview of the top live streaming platforms and what sets each one apart. By the end, you'll know exactly which platform fits your needs. These are all very different options with unique advantages. Even so, you don't have to pick just one. With multistreaming software (like Riverside!), you can stream to multiple platforms at the same time. Key takeaways include defining your goals, identifying your audience, and deciding how to monetize your content. Live streaming platforms like YouTube Live and Facebook Live have an established audience of viewers you should try to reach. The article covers YouTube Live (best for building an audience from scratch), Facebook Live (best for businesses), Instagram Live (best for influencers), TikTok Live (best for entertainers), Twitch (best for gamers), LinkedIn Live (best for B2B), Kick (best for revenue share), Uscreen (best for video-on-demand), Dacast (best for enterprises), and Vimeo Live (best for branded content).",
